<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State.</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-05"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 5, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your communication of the 30th ultimo, relative to the
                            refusal of a clearance to Messrs. Darrell &amp; Nash on merchandise
                            shipped by them to Nassau, and, in reply, to inform your lordship that I
                            have transmitted a copy thereof to the Secretary of the Treasury, who
                            has been requested to investigate the case, with a view to the adoption
                            of such proceedings as the result may warrant.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, my lord, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD,</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>